<p class="page" id="a6521205">[Page 205]</p>
<p>to have the "purple pup" over here, if they would be allowed but unfortunately there is no place for mascots on the ration strength.</p>
<p>I am lucky in still having my same old charger which I brought with me from the 8th Battery, as riding horses are very hard to obtain out of any of the drafts of remounts that come along.</p>
<p>Colonel Rosenthal (or I should say General now) is still going strong and was asking me lately to remember him to you when next writing.</p>
<p>Your skit on the temperance cranks reads splendidly. We have an Irish doc in this Brigade Mick O'Riordan and he happened to be in my tent while I was reading it and I thought he would have convulsions.</p>
